createPtnCut(25.10)                                        createPtnCut(25.10)

Name
       createPtnCut - Creates a partition rectangular cut from a partition

Syntax
       createPtnCut

       [-help]

       [-ptn <string>]

       <x1 y1 x2 y2>

       Creates  a  partition rectangular cut from a partition. This object can
       be created after specifying a module guide to be a partition. Rectangu-
       lar cuts can only occur on the edge of the partition guide. You can use
       this command after specifying partition.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs a brief description that includes the type  and  default
              information  for each createPtnCut parameter. For a detailed de-
              scription of the command and all of its parameters, use the  man
              command:

              man createPtnCut

       <x1 y1 x2 y2>
              Specifies the coordinates of the cut area (x1 y1 x2 y2 ).

              Data_type: rect, required

       -ptn <string>
              Specifies  a partition to create a partition cut. If this option
              is not selected, the command loops through all the partitions an
              attempts to find the overlapped partition, then creates a parti-
              tion cut for that partition.

              Data_type: string, optional

Example
       The following command creates a partition cut area to modify a  rectan-
       gular partition:

       createPtnCut 2353.8000 7123.000 2653.8000 8298.2000

Related Information
              * Partitioning the Design chapter in the Innovus User Guide

